This paper is primarily focused on optimization methods in machine learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses stochastic differential equations (SDEs) to study the role of memory in optimization, which could potentially fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of adaptive methods such as Adam and RMSprop, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
